# Advanced Audio Stem Separator

[![Website](https://img.shields.io/badge/Website-Live-brightgreen)](https://vicsanity623.github.io)
[![Discord](https://img.shields.io/badge/Discord-Join_Community-5865F2?logo=discord&logoColor=white)](https://discord.gg/75DwcRM3Y)

<br>

A professional, 100% free web-based tool that separates audio tracks into individual stems (**Vocals, Drums, Bass, Other**) using the state-of-the-art **Demucs** AI engine.

**üîó Try it now: [vicsanity623.github.io](https://vicsanity623.github.io)**

---

## üéß New Features (v2.0)

We have completely overhauled the interface to provide a studio-quality experience:

- **üåä Visual Waveforms**  
  Real-time waveform rendering for every separated track using *WaveSurfer.js*.

- **üéõÔ∏è Smart Player**  
  "Solo Mode" playback ‚Äî clicking play on one stem automatically mutes the others for critical listening.

- **‚¨áÔ∏è Flexible Downloads**  
  Download individual stems (WAV) or grab everything in a single ZIP file.

- **üöÄ Real-Time Progress**  
  Live feedback and percentage tracking during the AI separation process.

- **üîì Seamless Connection**  
  No configuration required. The frontend automatically connects to backend nodes.

---

## üß† Powered by Demucs

This service utilizes the  
[**Demucs (Hybrid Transformer)**](https://github.com/facebookresearch/demucs)  
audio source separation engine developed by Meta AI Research.

- **Model:** `htdemucs` (High-performance hybrid transformer)
- **Quality:** Professional-grade separation
- **Architecture:** 4-stem separation  
  *(Vocals, Drums, Bass, Other)*

---

## ‚ö†Ô∏è Server Status & Performance Note

**Please Read:**  
This service is hosted on volunteer hardware (Intel-based architecture) and runs on **CPU processing**.

- **Processing Time:**  
  It may take **2‚Äì5 minutes** to process a standard song.

- **Availability:**  
  If the site hangs or does not connect, the host machine may be offline for maintenance or cooling.

- **Queue:**  
  If multiple users attempt to process files simultaneously, you may experience delays.

